Document specific. More of a chrome thing than document "view"

Essentially just there for the keyboard shortcuts. No one is going to use these from the menu item.

text.tspan: Version 2: text entry with drop down
Elements from each version can be combined: one control could be a menu button and another a text entry with drop down.
Places controls in order of importance: current page, zoom level, search, more actions.

flowRoot.flowPara: Button turns into a text entry field when pressed.
Unclear why anyone would ever not want this.
"Dual" alone is confusing. Dual what? What's the opposite of dual? It would be better to automatically switch between single and dual depending on the zoom level and window size.
Seems odd to have navigation controls mixed with view controls. Makes the purpose of the menu less clear.
There's already a separate control for zooming. Having zoom controls in different places seems odd.
Unclear why this is necessary. Shouldn't Evince detect if the file has changed?
Confusing. Sounds like it creates a copy, like Save a Copy.
Odd to see Save a Copy without Save and Save As... As a result, it is unclear what the purpose of this option is.
Label is a bit misleading - sounds like a generic function, rather than being email-specific. "Email as Attachment" would be more appropriate?
Doesn't work if there isn't a user visible folder (eg. viewing an email attachment). Seems like this would be better and clearer from the Properties dialog.
Contextual action - unclear what will be copied. Context menu is a better home for this.
Contextual action - unclear what will be copied.
There's no way to inspect what the current defaults are, change them individually, or revert settings changes. Would be better as a set of application preferences.
